<br>
Blaming the fail on the person who pulled Naggy is complete crap.  If people buggered off during the CR and res'ing from that, those people shouldn't have been on the raid in the first place.<br>
<br>
If you wuss out and head home with your metaphorical tail between your legs at the first sign of trouble, please, do everyone a favor and don't leave the precious safety of your home in the first place.<br>
<br>
Raids are dangerous.  There <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WILL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be setbacks.  There <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WILL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be long, painful CR's.  There <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WILL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be mistakes made.  There will, even, on occasion, be problems that have not yet been encountered (I, for one, would have sworn up and down until last night that Nagafen couldn't leave his lair... that's the first time I've seen that happen).<br>
<br>
But blaming the person who made a single mistake and pulled the dragon out of the lair is being pretty short-sighted.  Vox leaves her lair all the time.  She has been pulled to the buffline, and far beyond, a large number of times.  There have been partial wipes, people caught in bind-death-loops, giants respawning and killing people as they log back in to help, and numerous other problems.  In the past, we've dealt with it, stuck around, and got the job done anyway.<br>
<br>
Telling the person to loot un-rez'd corpses and leave the raid is totally un-called for, except in the most extreme cases (some who is, purposefully training the raid multiple times, for instance).<br>
<br>
Like Vree, I have a fair amount of issues with the buffs that were set up and given last night.<br>
<br>
To anyone planning on running a buffline for Nagafen or Vox in the future, please, read this thread:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showMessage?topicID=303.topic">pub140.ezboard.com/fcounc...=303.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Also, a few words about specific buffs and the order they should be given.<br>
<br>
1) Endure vs Resist<br>
Using Endure &lt;poison/disease/cold/fire&gt; instead of Resist &lt;same&gt; is unnacceptable.  Endure buffs are dispelled far more easily than resist buffs, making them useless as junk buffs to buffer the &quot;important&quot; buffs (namely, the magic resist and fire/cold resist buff for the dragon in question).  Never, ever, use Endure &lt;anything&gt; as a junk buff.  Period.<br>
<br>
2) Stat buffs<br>
Even accounting for a relative lack of Shaman on the raid, there were stat buffs that could have been put on.  Druids can cast Storm Strength or Girdle of Karana (both fairly tough to dispell), and rangers can cast Feet like Cat (or whatever their Agi buff is called).<br>
<br>
3) Ranger ATK buff vs Brell's HP buffs<br>
Brell's Steadfast Aegis and Brells Mountinous Barrier are both extremely hard to dispell (BMB has something like 36 counters, enough to last through 2 fully un-resisted dispell blasts from Nagafen, which do about 18 counters a piece from what I've seen) - ranger ATK buffs are far easier to dispell, and don't provide as many hp, which is far more important than adding a couple points of melee damage from the higher atk rating.  Oh yeah, they don't stack... something that someone setting up a buffline should know before they take the job, or something they should be told by the buffers as soon as they try to set up the line with both being cast.<br>
<br>
4) Cleric AC Buff<br>
There was no AC buff given.  While AC may only be useful if you are being melee'd by Naggy, Shield of Words and higher AC buffs are tough to dispell.  And ultimately, EVERY BUFF put in front of MR and CR/FR buffs is basically there to be a shield first, and a useful buff second.<br>
<br>
5) Circle of Summer/Winter placement<br>
Circle of Summer/Winter should, always, in every case, without exception, be the LAST BUFF IN THE LINEUP.  Never, ever, should it be put before Symbol, for example, which was the case last night.<br>
<br>
6) Mana/Mind buffs<br>
